# Cross-build and static smbd environment.
# Samba 4.24 marks some generated tools as hostcc but still lets waf inherit
# target compiler/linker settings. Keep those host tools on the VM compiler,
# while applying static link flags only to the smbd binary we deploy.
0001-waf-cross-static-env.patch|waf hostcc and static smbd environment

# NetBSD runtime compatibility.
# NetBSD4 lacks newer libc symbols, and the runtime kernels are older than the
# SDKs used to compile these binaries. Keep normal file serving on path-based
# VFS fallbacks instead of relying on runtime *at/openat2/fdopendir support.
0002-netbsd4-libreplace-compat.patch|NetBSD4 libc compatibility shims
0003-netbsd-vfs-runtime-fallbacks.patch|Time Capsule VFS runtime syscall fallbacks
# NetBSD4 can lose Samba's cached is_directory flag even when stat still says
# the handle is a directory; recover before rejecting SMB2 QUERY_DIRECTORY.
0004-netbsd4-query-directory-stat-fallback.patch|NetBSD4 SMB2 directory stat fallback

# Single-binary smbd behavior.
# Finder and smbclient enumerate shares through IPC$ srvsvc. Embed that one
# pipe in smbd because the Time Capsule RAM-disk deployment cannot rely on
# external DCE/RPC helper binaries living on an Apple-managed HFS disk.
0005-smbd-embedded-srvsvc.patch|embedded srvsvc named pipe support
# smbd -V exits through shared option parsing before server.c can clean up.
0006-smbd-version-no-dangling-frame.patch|clean smbd version exit
# Reopened TDB handles should not leak into any helper exec path.
0007-tdb-cloexec-compat.patch|TDB close-on-exec compatibility

# No-pthread appliance runtime behavior.
# Time Capsule kernels do not support the pthread behavior Samba 4.24 expects.
# Host long-lived notifyd/cleanupd/scavenger work in the smbd parent event loop
# and avoid helper forks that hit raw abort paths on these targets.
0008-no-pthread-smbd-daemons-in-parent.patch|host smbd helper services in the parent event loop
# Avoid pthreadpool-backed messaging paths and watched SMBX DB wrappers that
# depend on filtered-reader invalidation machinery unsafe in this build.
0009-no-pthread-messaging-and-db-fallbacks.patch|no-pthread messaging and SMBX DB fallbacks
# The static appliance build does not launch winbindd; keep local mappings and
# skip libwbclient lookups for the remaining Windows SIDs during startup.
0010-no-pthread-local-sid-to-unixids.patch|local SID mapping without winbindd
# smbXsrv_version_global_init retains global DB state after returning; parent
# it to an explicit named context instead of the process-global talloc stack.
0011-no-pthread-smbxsrv-version-global-parent.patch|explicit parent for retained SMBX version state
# tevent's pooled request, call-depth, and threaded-context paths assume
# pthread/TLS behavior that the appliance build removes after configure.
0012-no-pthread-tevent-fallbacks.patch|tevent fallbacks for no-pthread builds
# Configure may see pthread/TLS on the VM before the target cache is scrubbed;
# make the final no-pthread build use process-global storage for __thread uses.
0013-no-pthread-tls-fallbacks.patch|no-pthread TLS configure and __thread fallback

# Static build compile fixes.
# This reduced nonshared build can expose duplicate typedefs through multiple
# include paths; guard the typedefs instead of relying on fragile include order.
0014-typedef-guards.patch|duplicate typedef guards
# NetBSD4 lacks posix_spawn, but local named pipe and print queue code still
# compile into the static smbd target even though printing is not enabled.
0015-netbsd-posix-spawn-fallbacks.patch|NetBSD posix_spawn fallbacks
# Samba's bundled popt fallback collides with libc glob_pattern_p in the static
# NetBSD lanes; rename the bundled private symbol.
0016-popt-glob-symbol-rename.patch|bundled popt glob symbol rename
# Time Capsule lock databases live on a tiny RAM disk. Let smb.conf force
# volatile dbwrap TDB deletes onto the global freelist instead of retaining
# thousands of per-hash-chain dead records after Time Machine closes files.
0017-dbwrap-tdb-max-dead-config.patch|configurable dbwrap TDB max-dead records
